:END:
https://careercaddy.online/job-applications/92
[2026-04-23] Timeline pills read right ("Unvetted → Vetted Good →
Applied → Contact") because they branch off =jobApplication.status=,
but STATUS HISTORY reads =applicationStatuses= hasMany — and Ember
Data was getting an empty relationship, so blank list, so no way
to click into an entry to add a note.

Two-line fix:
- =api/job_hunting/api/serializers.py::JobApplicationSerializer= —
  add =linked_relationships = ["application-statuses"]= so the
  to-many relationship emits =data: [...]= linkage instead of the
  spec-compliant links-only form (other to-many rels do the same
  thing; this one was missing).
- =frontend/app/routes/job-applications/show.js= —
  =findRecord= now passes =include: "application-statuses"= so the
  API sideloads the records in the =included= array for Ember to
  match against the linkage.

Tests: =api/.../test_job_application_status_history.py= pins the
linkage shape and the sideload.

