[2026-04-20 api+frontend] =Resume.file_path= already existed on the
model; the ingest endpoint wasn't populating it. Now
=/api/v1/resumes/ingest/= stashes =uploaded_file.name= on the
placeholder Resume synchronously. Browsers only hand over the filename
(no client-side path), so =file_path= is treated as a human-readable
"where did this come from" marker — the server doesn't retain the
blob, and the frontend renders it as plain text (no link target) in
=components/resumes/title/form.hbs= below the Resume Notes field.
Clone still carries =file_path= forward so derivative resumes can
trace back to the originating import.
This will help the user remember where that file was once there is some drift in the derivative versions

