[2026-04-23] =make ci= failed with
=RenderCompositorSWGL failed mapping default framebuffer, no dt=
+ =glxtest: libpci missing, libGL.so.1 missing= in the build-frontend
Dagger container (node:20-slim + firefox-esr). Root cause: headless
Firefox under SWGL compositor still wants /dev/dri, and the container
was missing =libpci3=/=libgl1=/=libegl1= + had no virtual framebuffer.
Fix (=dagger/src/career_caddy_pipeline.py::build_frontend=):
- Install =libpci3 libgl1 libegl1 libdbus-glib-1-2 libgtk-3-0
  libasound2 xvfb= alongside firefox-esr.
- Wrap the test step with =xvfb-run -a npm run test:ember= so Firefox
  has a virtual framebuffer to render into.
- Export =MOZ_HEADLESS=1= as defense-in-depth.

* DONE =make poller= hit localhost when =.env.local= was present [parent] :bug:
CLOSED: [2026-04-23]
:PROPERTIES:
:ARCHIVE_TIME: 2026-04-23 Thu 19:34
:ARCHIVE_FILE: ~/Network/syncthing/Projects/career_caddy/todo.org
:ARCHIVE_OLPATH: Bugs 🐛
:ARCHIVE_CATEGORY: todo
:ARCHIVE_TODO: DONE
:END:
[2026-04-23] The =poller= target was =cd ai && uv run caddy-poller=,
relying on inherited =CC_API_BASE_URL=. When a user has =.env.local=
with =CC_API_BASE_URL=http://localhost:8000= at repo root, =uv run=
(or some other dotenv consumer in the chain) picked that up despite
the shell env pointing at prod — so =make poller= silently hit local.
Fix: =Makefile= =poller= target now sets =CC_API_BASE_URL= explicitly
to =$${CC_API_BASE_URL_PROD:-https://api.careercaddy.online}=,
mirroring =poller-local='s explicit-override pattern. Matches the
"pick an explicit target and force the env" rule already used by
=poller-local=.

