[2026-04-23] Root cause: =components/answers/form.js::toggleFavorite=
called =answer.save()= unconditionally. On =/answers/new= the record
is unsaved, so =save()= POSTed an invalid (empty-content) payload, the
catch branch rolled =favorite= back to =false=, and the user's toggle
never survived the form submit. Fix: early-return before =save()= when
=answer.isNew= — the flipped attr rides along with the main form
submit. On =/answers/edit= the flip-and-save behavior is preserved.

