[2026-04-18 ai+frontend] Landed as a single change this session.
Three action shapes now supported by =ChatMessageComponent.runAction=;
agent prompts (main chat + onboarding sub-agent) updated to prefer
the zero-LLM variants.

Shapes emitted by the agent:
- ={"label": "...", "navigate": "/path"}= → =router.transitionTo= (no LLM turn)
- ={"label": "...", "model": {"type": T, "id": N, "patch": {...}}}=
  → =store.peekRecord(T, N).setProperties(patch).save()= via a
  per-type allow-list in =message.js= (resume/cover-letter/answer/
  job-post: favorite only + a few safe sibling fields; user:
  onboarding sub-keys only). Unknown types / disallowed keys are
  dropped silently.
- ={"label": "...", "message": "..."}= → existing chat turn (legacy)

Rolled out to ALL users, not just staff — per product decision this
is the desired UX.

Follow-ups (if we hit them):
- Warning toast when an agent emits an unsupported patch so we can
  tighten the prompts without silent drops.
- Analytics on which action shape the agent picks most often, to
  calibrate prompt tightness.

* DONE Chat: no editing linked resume resources; disambiguate "title" :APPROVED:
CLOSED: [2026-04-18 Fri]
:PROPERTIES:
:ARCHIVE_TIME: 2026-04-23 Thu 19:44
