[2026-04-18 api] Account-takeover-class gap: =_upsert= at
=api/job_hunting/api/views/users.py:437= had no ownership gate, so any
authenticated user could =PATCH /api/v1/users/{other_id}/= and overwrite
another account's =password=, =email=, =phone=, =linkedin=, =github=,
=address=, =links=, =first_name=, =last_name=, =onboarding=. Only
=is_staff= / =is_active= were gated (they already return 403). Found
during Agent Wizard review of the Ember-inspector tampering surface.

Fix: added
=if not request.user.is_staff and user.id != request.user.id: 403=
at the top of =_upsert=, mirroring the guard =retrieve= has at line 222.
Tests in =tests/test_user_upsert_ownership.py=: 7 cases covering PATCH
self, PATCH other (incl. password + onboarding), PUT other, and staff
override. Reconciles =api/SECURITY_AUDIT.md='s "5 detail actions"
matrix claim — update/partial_update were missed in the original audit
scope.

Follow-up (not blocking; own ticket): require current-password
re-authentication for password change, even when changing your own.

