[2026-04-23 api] Two-part fix:
- =filter[query]= on the job-posts list now OR's against
  =link__icontains= so a pasted URL in the search bar finds the
  existing post. Was searching only title/description/company. Tests
  in =test_job_post_query_filter_link.py=.
- =POST /api/v1/scrapes/from-text/= now short-circuits with 409
  when =link= maps to a non-stub JobPost — re-parsing a fully-
  extracted post wastes the LLM call and overwrites the user's
  data. Stubs (thin/empty description) still pass through so the
  existing =updated_stub= path can fill them in. Body =force=true=
  overrides. Frontend paste form catches 409 and shows a sticky
  banner with two actions: "Open job post #N" or "Re-parse anyway".
  Tests in =test_scrape_from_text.py::TestScrapeFromTextDuplicateLink=.

