Filed earlier today when the symptom was misread as "extension push provides no UI feedback." Investigation confirmed the extension actually does fire an OS notification ("scored N ✓ TITLE") and the underlying scrape was correctly linked to jp 1428 via fingerprint dedupe (Score 143 attached to jp 1428, top_score=15 confirms). The user's real concern was twofold and both branches are tracked separately:
- The =/jp.show/= duplicate-candidate banner shipped on branch =feat/jp-duplicate-candidates= (parent commit 423f652).
- cc_auto hallucination producing jp 1724 with mismatched link/title/company is open as a sibling Inbox/Bug entry above.

Closing to keep the Inbox honest. Original brief follows for forensic context.

Repro (production, 2026-05-04 -> 2026-05-05):
- jp 1724 (Junior to Mid Level Full Stack Developer, source=email) created by cc_auto at 23:04 UTC.
- User opened jp 1724 in browser; the source URL is a ZipRecruiter /km/AAGj-... tracking link that (when followed) lands on a /jobs/snbl-usa-...?expired_link=1 page (a different job).
- User clicked the extension popup. Extension grabbed body.innerText + location.href and POSTed /api/v1/scrapes/from-text/ (source=extension, link=resolved /jobs/snbl-usa-...).
- API: created Scrape 323 (status=pending), called parse_scrape sync. parse() ran the LLM, extracted SNBL bilingual BD job. Cold-create get_or_create(title, company) matched the EXISTING jp 1428 (cc_auto-stub from 2026-04-29, same title+company). last_outcome=duplicate_via_fingerprint. Scrape 323 linked to jp 1428.
- Auto-score fired against jp 1428: Score 143, value=15. (jp1428.top_score is 15 -- matches.)
- Extension background.js polled scrape 323 -> terminal completed -> POST score (already done by from_text but extension does it again? to confirm) -> OS notification fires "Career Caddy -- scored 15 ✓ START UP BUS DEV & PROG MGR ...".

User outcome: viewed /job-posts/1724, saw no scrape, reported "didn't land." The scrape DID land -- on jp 1428. The user has no path to discover that.

Verified state via MCP:
- find_job_post_by_link(scrape 323's url) -> [] (jp 1428 still holds its old /km/AAH... tracking link, never updated to the canonical /jobs/snbl-usa-... URL the new scrape resolved).
- get_scores(job_post_id=1428) -> Score 143 (the one auto-fired by from_text). Confirms scrape 323 -> jp 1428.
- search_job_posts("START UP BUS DEV") -> jp 999 + jp 1428 (two existing dupes of the SNBL job from earlier email scrapes; their /km/ links differ per-recipient so canonical_link dedupe could never collapse them).

Premier-feature gaps to close (from_text is the extension's selling point):

A. Response payload contract -- /scrapes/from-text/ returns ONLY the Scrape resource. The extension has to do a follow-up GET include=job-post to learn where it landed. Make the response include the JobPost id + title + outcome (created / duplicate_via_link / duplicate_via_fingerprint / updated_stub / updated_stub_via_fingerprint) inline, e.g.
  {data: <scrape>, meta: {job_post: {id, title, frontend_url, outcome}}}

B. Extension popup feedback -- popup currently shows fire-and-forget "Sent ✓ -- watch for a notification." before closing. Should display a result card with the resolved JobPost title + clickable link (target=_blank to the jp frontend_url), and surface dedupe outcome ("linked to existing post" vs "created new").

C. Notification click action -- background.js fires a plain notification with the title. Add a click handler that opens the resulting jp's frontend URL. MV3 supports api.notifications.onClicked.

D. Data-hygiene: when parse_scrape hits duplicate_via_fingerprint and the new scrape.url is more canonical than the existing job_post.link (e.g. existing has /km/<token> tracking URL, new has /jobs/<slug> resolved URL), upgrade JobPost.link + canonical_link. Tests exist for stub-merging but not for link-canonicalization on dupe.

E. Pre-existing fingerprint-dedupe gap -- jp 999 and jp 1428 are dupes of the same job that fingerprint dedupe never collapsed because their titles differ by a trailing suffix ("75-100% FTE"). Worth a normalizer: lowercase + strip trailing FTE/percentage/parens for the get_or_create lookup, while preserving the original on display.

Tags: extension, dedupe, api, frontend, bugs

Code touchpoints:
- api/job_hunting/api/views/scrapes.py from_text (lines 582-711): build the meta block on the response.
- api/job_hunting/lib/parsers/job_post_extractor.py process_evaluation duplicate_via_fingerprint branch (lines 451-467): add link-canonicalization upgrade.
- frontend/public/extensions/career-caddy-sender/popup.js (sendBtn handler 344-460): show result card before window.close.
- frontend/public/extensions/career-caddy-sender/background.js (notify, pollScrapeOnce, pollScoreOnce): add notifications.onClicked handler with stored frontendUrl.

Tests to add:
- test_from_text_response_includes_resolved_job_post (no mock; parse_scrape stubbed to set scrape.job_post_id)
- test_from_text_response_meta_outcome_for_duplicate_via_fingerprint
- test_duplicate_via_fingerprint_upgrades_link_when_more_canonical

