Filed as the very first read on the symptom; verified wrong. Scrape 323 was correctly linked to jp 1428 via the =duplicate_via_fingerprint= path in JobPostExtractor (matched on title + company). The auto-score in =from_text= subsequently fired against jp 1428 (Score 143, value 15 = jp 1428.top_score). No orphan. The actual root cause was upstream cc_auto hallucination on jp 1724 (sibling Inbox/Bug entry). Closing.

Original brief follows for forensic context.

Repro: extension v0.3.6 pushed page text from a ZipRecruiter listing on 2026-05-05 01:08:38 UTC.

Result:
- POST /api/v1/scrapes/from-text/ -> 202
- Scrape 323 created (SNBL bilingual BD job, full content extracted)
- Score 143 created
- NO JobPost created; scrape not attached to any existing JobPost
- search_job_posts "SNBL Japanese" returns 0; latest JobPost ids unchanged after the push

User symptom: opened /job-posts/1724 expecting to see the scrape; jp 1724 is an unrelated email-sourced Junior Full Stack Developer post created by cc_auto an hour earlier. Frontend GET /api/v1/job-posts/1724/?include=scrapes returns no scrapes (correct -- they are not linked).

Root cause hypotheses (need to read api views/scrapes.py from-text action):
1. from-text view writes Scrape + Score but never creates/links a JobPost.
2. Even if it tried to dedupe by canonical_link, the email path stores tracking links (ziprecruiter.com/km/AAGj-...) while the extension push has the resolved canonical (ziprecruiter.com/jobs/snbl-usa-...). Different strings -> no canonical match. Need fingerprint-based dedupe per Architecture/URL storage + dedupe pipeline; see feedback memory dedupe-first-on-new-write-paths.

Logfire trace: 2026-05-05T01:08:38Z, span POST /api/v1/scrapes/from-text/, Firefox UA on Linux.

Fix scope:
- from-text must either (a) create a JobPost and link the scrape, or (b) dedupe to existing jp via fingerprint + canonical and link to that.
- Decide: does extension push always create a new jp, or look up first? Probably look up by canonical_link after url_rewrites normalization, fall back to fingerprint, only create if neither matches.
- Score 143 also dangles -- needs same job_post linkage.

Tags: extension, dedupe, api, bugs, scrape

