   Scrape 298 (=jobs/view/4407097463=) ran 4× today: 1 success, 3
   =ExtractFail=. The 3 failures hit LinkedIn's documented SDUI
   partial-render state — top card + Premium card + hiring-team card
   render but the =About the job= subtree never lands in the DOM.
   Profile id=2 already documents this in =extraction_hints= and
   instructs the LLM to emit a placeholder description string
   ("[DESCRIPTION NOT CAPTURED — LinkedIn page rendered only the top
   card …]") while still extracting title/company/location/salary
   from the visible card. But on every fail run today,
   =EvaluateExtraction= bins the Tier1Mini output as fail, routes to
   =Tier2Haiku= (which no-ops in 130-150ms), then to =ExtractFail=.
   The placeholder path is never honored.

   Files to inspect:
   - =agents/scrape_graph/nodes/evaluate_extraction.py= — what is the
     pass/fail rule and does it special-case the placeholder string
     or =description.length < N=?
   - =agents/scrape_graph/nodes/tier1_mini.py= /
     =agents/scrape_graph/nodes/tier2_haiku.py= — are the prompts
     even given the relevant hints from =extraction_hints=, and is
     the placeholder string in the prompt?
   - =agents/scrape_graph/nodes/persist_job_post.py= — would saving
     a JobPost with the placeholder description and =is_partial=
     (or similar) flag be acceptable downstream?

   Smallest test that would catch the regression: feed a fixture
   matching the persisted =job_content= for scrape 298 (top card +
   "Use AI to assess how you fit" + "Looking for talent?" + footer,
   no responsibilities prose) into the extract pipeline and assert
   it produces a JobPost with the documented placeholder description
   rather than =ExtractFail=. Fixture text is in the stored html for
   scrape 298 (id=298).

   Trace evidence: =mcp_get_scrape_graph_trace scrape_id=298= shows
   four full runs, the 08:49 success matched =h2:has-text("About the
   job")= in 18ms, and the three failures all timed out the entire
   19-selector list with =matched_selector=null=. Logfire confirms
   =Scrape 298 graph done outcome=success job_post_id=1650 tiers=2=
   for the 08:49 run.


