:ARCHIVE_CATEGORY: todo
:ARCHIVE_TODO: TODO
:ARCHIVE_ITAGS: IMPORTANT
:END:

Prod-only crash. The /reports/application-flow page threw Uncaught
(in promise) Error: circular link from d3-sankey computeNodeDepths.
Network was clean (api returned 1.06 KB OK); the cycle was in the
payload itself.

Root cause: api/job_hunting/lib/services/application_flow.py
_app_bucket_sequence walked status logs chronologically with no
monotonicity check. Real-world prod logs like Applied → Rejected →
Interview Scheduled (a correction to a mis-logged Rejection) emitted
back-edges that produced cycles in the aggregate Sankey graph.
Local/test data never generated corrections so the bug never
reproduced.

Fix: STAGE_RANKS (applied=1 / interview=2 / offer=3 / terminals=4),
then pop-on-backward in _app_bucket_sequence — a status with rank ≤
top of sequence is read as a correction to a mis-logged prior status
and pops it. Latest log wins; resulting per-app sequence is
monotonic, aggregate is always a DAG. Ghost-gate uses surviving tail
timestamp, not popped one.

Frontend defensive guard: components/reports/application-flow-sankey.{js,hbs}
now wraps layout(...) in try/catch and renders an inline amber
banner instead of crashing the route if a cycle slips through.

Skeleton: templates/reports/application-flow/loading.hbs replaced
with a layout-matching shimmer (subnav, header + counts, filter bar,
5-column funnel-shaped sankey placeholder). Pure Tailwind, no JS.
Makes the page feel snappy during the ~2s api call.

Tests:
- api: 5 new application-flow tests (correction drops misread,
  mid-funnel correction, terminal→terminal correction, cross-app
  DAG aggregate, aged-correction ghost timestamp). 21/21 pass.
- frontend: 3 new sankey integration tests (DAG happy path, cyclic
  rescue, empty payload). All in tests/integration/components/reports/.

Verify: make ci → frontend 328/328, api 891/891.

